cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on robotic pick-and-place tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses instance and semantic segmentation, which are topics related to computer vision (cs.CV). The joint learning approach proposed in the paper involves fusing instance- and image-level reasoning, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed approach in achieving real-world robotic tasks, which could be related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) in terms of ensuring the safety and security of the robotic system.
